{"id":"white","term":"White","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A symbol of purity (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 5:12\">2 Chr. 5:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 51:7\">Ps. 51:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 1:18\">Isa. 1:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 3:18\">Rev. 3:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 7:14\">7:14</a>). Our Lord, at his transfiguration, appeared in raiment “white as the light” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 17:2\">Matt. 17:2</a>, etc.).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["2 Chronicles 5:12","Psalms 51:7","Isaiah 1:18","Revelation 3:18","Revelation 7:14","Matthew 17:2"]}